description: Seven Days in Summer: Countdown to Partition Sociopolitical Documentary hosted by Ayesha Dharker, published by BBC in 2017 - English narration http://docuwiki.net/images/8/8a/Seven-Days-in-Summer-Countdown-to-Partition-Cover.jpg Information ------------------------------ Seven Days in Summer: Countdown to Partition Today India and Pakistan are home to one fifth of the world's population. They are rising powers but hostile neighbours. Their enmity can be traced back to the week of their birth, 70 years ago. On 15 August 1947, Britain would give up the Indian Empire, partitioning it in into two independent countries, India and Pakistan. This film tells the story of the seven days that led up to their independence and the last days of the British Raj.
